<br>
Her hand reached out and gently touched Hippolyte's forearm above the bracer.  &quot;How is Gabby?&quot;  The warrior knew very well that Gabby had run off to be with Xena.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hippolyte>Hippolyte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 785<br> <font color=#993300>(2/21/03 6:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=55>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/Hippwknife1ezboard.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Preparing for the attack</span><hr size=1> With a flick of the wrist, Hippolyte suddenly grabbed Elektra by the arm and held Elektra's fingers away from her skin.  &quot;Gabby is fine.  Now.. Elektra... if you would listen to me.. now.  Prepare your weapons.&quot;  Her brown eyes were serious as her brow furrowed a bit, looking up at the taller warrior. <p>@xxx}}::::::::::::::::::::>

"We ride tonight!  With the strength that Hera has given
us-- and the strength that we have _earned_ for ourselves!  Take
what you need, but be quick.  Stay only until the sound of horn.
The moment you hear it-- we ride away.  Now-- to your horses."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elektraamazon>Elektra Amazon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#993300>(2/21/03 6:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=56>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/ddelektradd/images/smelek.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Preparing for the attack</span><hr size=1> Hippolyte's grip on her arm had been tight, as the amazon now rubbed her arm a bit with her other hand.  &quot;Yes, Vasilissa,&quot; replied Elektra.  Surprised at Hippolyte's move.   The years had changed Hippolyte it seemed.  But, the amazon knew it would only be a matter of time.  Soon, Hippolyte would call her old lover back to her bed.<br>
<br>
Elektra tilted her head in respect and then turned around moving into the woods.  Her weapons were always prepared.  Sharpened each night to be ready for blood.  But, this attack could use a little something extra.  Elektra broke off branches and and began to fashion weapons from the wood.  Long spears would come in handy for the night. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=marpeamzn>Marpe Amzn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#993300>(2/21/03 6:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=57>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/MarpeAmznrpg.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Preparing for the attack</span><hr size=1> The guard had already taken off into the woods close to the Roman village.  Stepping quietly, she listened for any sound of danger.  Her eyes slowely covered the ground and the trees.  Much of the area seemed thick and perfect for an ambush.  But, there was not set trail. There were three in fact, all seeming to go in the direction of the Black Sea.  <br>
<br>
A snap caught Marpe's attention and the amazon quickly scrambled up into the dense trees.  Watching soon, she found the source of the snap.  Three men were walking around searching for something, or someone.  They were grumbling in a language that Marpe could not quite understand.  Surely, they were the Romans.  For about an hour, the guard watched as the men moved back and forth.  It looked like they were searching for marks in the ground.  Perhaps, still looking for Hippolyte.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hippolyte>Hippolyte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 786<br> <font color=#993300>(2/21/03 6:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=58>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/Hippwknife1ezboard.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Preparing for the attack</span><hr size=1> For a moment, Hippolyte watched as Elektra walked into the woods.  Then gently shaking her head, Hipp turned her attention back to the saddle bag on athe back of her mare.  Pulling out weapons and inspecting each, Hippolyte slid them all to their proper places.  Each weapon had a home. A place where her hands would move on instinct.  <br>
<br>
As she worked, Hippolyte's thoughts were on Elektra.  She was a bit irritated by Elektra's obvious move on her.   In the old days...that would have got to Hippolyte.  But, Hipp knew too well about Elektra's love.  It was quick and then gone....like the warrior. <p>@xxx}}::::::::::::::::::::>

"We ride tonight!  With the strength that Hera has given
us-- and the strength that we have _earned_ for ourselves!  Take
what you need, but be quick.  Stay only until the sound of horn.
The moment you hear it-- we ride away.  Now-- to your horses."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dawnithinia>Dawnithinia </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 440<br> <font color=#993300>(2/22/03 2:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=59>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Watching.</span><hr size=1>  Dawn for a moment stopped to watch Elektra and Hippolyte. For a brief second she stopped, hesitant on responding to the comments that Elektra made. She was leery of this amazon; emerald pools narrowed as she watched for one last moment. It wasn't her place to comment.<br>
<br>
 Shaking her head the assassin headed into the woods, her nose metaphorically to the ground as she worked. Once far enough from the camp, she latched onto a tree limb, pulled herself into the foliage and was gone. Only one of her own specie could track her from here. <br>
<br>
 It would be a matter of moments before she found the roman men, and then it would take all the assassin had to not kill them were they stood. But this was a joint fight, and doing so would only harm the trust her amazon sisters had in her. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=marpeamzn>Marpe Amzn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#993300>(2/23/03 12:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=60>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/MarpeAmznrpg.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Watching.</span><hr size=1> Finally, the Roman men started to walk back to their village.  Marpe watched them for a bit, and then slid down the side of the tree.  Landing with a soft thud, Marpe looked in the Roman's direction and then knowing they were truly gone.  She took off back to the camp.<br>
<br>
